The article is a transcript of a conversation between Vice President Kamala Harris and students at Reading Area Community College in Reading, Pennsylvania. Harris discusses various topics, including the importance of young leaders and their role in shaping the country's future. She emphasizes the significance of voting and encourages students to use their voices to bring about change. The conversation also touches on issues such as climate change, gun safety laws, and reproductive rights. Harris expresses her support for environmental policies that address the impact on low-income communities and advocates for common-sense gun safety measures while respecting the Second Amendment. She also discusses the importance of fighting for women's reproductive rights and ensuring that women have control over their own bodies. Harris concludes by urging students to have confidence in their own leadership abilities and to stand up for what they believe in.